      "comment": "AMERICAN EYES (8) suffered her first defeat in five starts last time out but was far from disgraced in coming from the back row for second at Pinjarra. Draws wider but she is a promising mare with plenty of upside and she finds a winnable race so can bounce back. LUCKY COPY (3) has been impressive in winning her last two outings at this circuit and distance, one from this barrier and the other from much wider. Big chance to land the hat trick. LOCH TAY (1) is another going well at this circuit and distance, finding winning form two back and clocking in second from this barrier last week. DELULU (9) draws out again but has done well to place in both starts since a spell and her fitness is building.",
